{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3ad6200f-6ab9-493c-b783-a7af3ba9793e","content":"Override `CreateWindow` in your `App.xaml.cs` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Resumed    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Activated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n\n    // iOS / Mac Catalyst only — fires when entering background\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical order:**  \n`Created → Activated → Resumed` on launch  \n`Deactivated → Stopped` when backgrounded  \n`Resumed → Activated` when foregrounded  \n`Destroying` on close  \n\n`Backgrounding` (iOS/Mac Catalyst) provides a `BackgroundingEventArgs` with a `State` dictionary you can use to persist data before suspension.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d0acc16-e4ea-46ab-b1d2-fde51f039d6c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question — I don't need to search the codebase for this. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the `Window` class exposes several lifecycle events:\n\n- `Created`\n- `Resumed`\n- `Activated`\n- `Deactivated`\n- `Stopped`\n- `Destroying`\n- `Backgrounding` (iOS/Mac Catalyst)\n\nYou can subscribe to these in your `App.xaml.cs` by overriding `CreateWindow`.","outputTokens":499,"requestId":"B7D2:19EA9:139D30:199FB3:69FFD7FD"},"id":"859ab43f-30d8-406a-a46d-5ba0d23f925f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:57:43.518Z","parentId":"3fdd0e68-27d6-4248-9462-99c135976e0b"}
